And it goes to eight.

00:33:27.840 --> 00:33:28.510
Then it goes to six.

00:33:28.510 --> 00:33:29.385
Then it goes to four.

00:33:29.385 --> 00:33:30.560
Then it goes to two, right?

00:33:30.560 --> 00:33:33.220
So you watched it
continue to get cheaper.

00:33:33.220 --> 00:33:36.560
There's a famous
investing joke that says,

00:33:36.560 --> 00:33:38.910
what do you call
market that's down 90%?

00:33:38.910 --> 00:33:40.840
That's a market
that was down 80%,

00:33:40.840 --> 00:33:44.010
and then proceeded to
go down 50% more, right?

00:33:44.010 --> 00:33:45.264
The way the math works out.

00:33:45.264 --> 00:33:46.680
And we talked about
this at lunch.

00:33:46.680 --> 00:33:50.040
The compounding that
people talk about-- eighth

00:33:50.040 --> 00:33:51.950
wonder the world is
compounding, right?

00:33:51.950 --> 00:33:55.156
Where if you just
invest long enough,

00:33:55.156 --> 00:33:56.280
it works out in your favor.

00:33:56.280 --> 00:33:58.580
Well, what they don't talk
about is the opposite.

00:33:58.580 --> 00:34:01.370
The bigger hole you get in, the
compounding works against you.

00:34:01.370 --> 00:34:03.370
So the kink doesn't
really happen

00:34:03.370 --> 00:34:05.480
until you lose about 10%
to 15% of your money.

00:34:05.480 --> 00:34:08.030
You lose 10%, it takes,
what 11 to get back to even?

00:34:08.030 --> 00:34:09.449
You lose 20, it takes 25.

00:34:09.449 --> 00:34:12.360
You lose 50, it takes
100% to get back to even.

00:34:12.360 --> 00:34:15.909
You lose 75%, it takes
300% to get back to even.

00:34:15.909 --> 00:34:17.989
You think 75% is unrealistic?

00:34:17.989 --> 00:34:20.130
US had a 90%
drawdown in the '30s.

00:34:20.130 --> 00:34:22.610
US has had multiple
50% draw downs.

00:34:22.610 --> 00:34:25.150
Every G10 country in the
world has lost at least 2/3

00:34:25.150 --> 00:34:27.030
